                            <entry>
                    <title>Global Day of Coderetreat 2016</title>
                    <link rel="alternate" href="http://coderetreat.org/xn/detail/6456126:BlogPost:53322"/>
                                        <id>tag:coderetreat.org,2016-04-09:6456126:BlogPost:53322</id>
                                        <updated>2016-04-09T16:30:00.000Z</updated>
                    
                                            <author>
                            <name>Ivan Kusalic</name>
                            <uri>http://coderetreat.org/profile/IvanKusalic</uri>
                        </author>
                    
                    <summary type="html">
                        &lt;p&gt;We are excited to announce the date for the Global Day of Coderetreat 2016!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This year GDCR will happen on &lt;strong&gt;Saturday, October 22nd&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thousands of developers all around the globe will get together on the same day to improve skills, share knowledge, practice together and generally have great time in a safe and fun environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last year, we had around 150 Coderetreats and 2,000 participants all over the globe joining us for the Global Day of Coderetreat. This…&lt;/p&gt;                    </summary>

                    <content type="html">
&lt;p&gt;We are excited to announce the date for the Global Day of Coderetreat 2016!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This year GDCR will happen on &lt;strong&gt;Saturday, October 22nd&lt;/strong&gt;!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thousands of developers all around the globe will get together on the same day to improve skills, share knowledge, practice together and generally have great time in a safe and fun environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Last year, we had around 150 Coderetreats and 2,000 participants all over the globe joining us for the Global Day of Coderetreat. This year we hope to have even more!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;What is a coderetreat? Coderetreat is a day­-long, intensive practice event focusing on the fundamentals of software development and design. The coderetreat format has proven itself to be a highly effective means of skill improvement by providing developers the opportunity to take part in focused practice away from the pressures of &#039;getting things done.&#039; For more information, check out the &lt;a href=&quot;http://gdcr.coderetreat.org/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;GDCR website&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GDCR 2016 Edition will be brought to you by hundreds of passionate local facilitators worldwide and a team of global coordinators, including &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/jthurne&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Jim Hurne&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/alinpandichi&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Alin Pandichi&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/rradczewski&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Raimo Radczewski&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/srbiv&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Stafford Brooke&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/ikusalic&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Ivan Kusalic&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Over the next couple of weeks, we will have more information about taking part in Global Day of Coderetreat 2016. Stay tuned by following &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/coderetreat&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;@coderetreat&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/search/?q=%23gdcr16&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;#gdcr16 hashtag&lt;/a&gt; on Twitter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hope you are as excited as we are and are looking forward to an amazing event! &lt;strong&gt;Don&#039;t forget&lt;/strong&gt; to add October 22nd to your calendars and spread the word.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;May the Cells be with you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/AXQI_kdSgso4BAo6gtAomkKsX6Auzg4lU0_sFAO-MpFCtuJn6NVUODRzEfetYB_l1wE3mOXQDpOuq1xXPrziZLM8pt2YF6ZQEGnRYqwVhr8uXxYncConlOE2qlgdXCZsKw&quot; height=&quot;79px;&quot; width=&quot;79px;&quot;/&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
